  "prompt": "Abandoned? Broken hearted granny how can I stop hurting?",
  "response": "I'm so sorry to hear you're feeling this way. Heartbreak is incredibly painful, especially when it feels like abandonment or loss. Here are some steps to help you heal and find peace:\n\n1. **Allow Yourself to Grieve**  \n   It\u2019s okay to feel hurt, sad, or angry. Give yourself permission to cry and process your emotions. Suppressing them will only prolong the pain.\n\n2. **Reach Out for Support**  \n   Talk to someone you trust\u2014a friend, family member, or counselor. Sharing your feelings can help ease the burden and remind you that you\u2019re not alone.\n\n3. **Practice Self-Compassion**  \n   Be kind to yourself. Remind yourself that you are loved and worthy, even if it doesn\u2019t feel that way right now. Treat yourself with the same care you\u2019d offer a dear friend.\n\n4. **Rediscover Your Passions**  \n   Reconnect with hobbies or activities that bring you joy. Whether it\u2019s gardening, reading, painting, or spending time in nature, doing things you love can help lift your spirits.\n\n5. **Focus on Small Wins**  \n   Celebrate the little victories\u2014getting out of bed, taking a walk, or making a meal. Each step forward is progress, no matter how small it feels.\n\n6. **Create a New Routine**  \n   Structure can bring comfort and a sense of normalcy. Try to establish a daily routine that includes healthy habits like eating well, sleeping enough, and staying active.\n\n7. **Practice Mindfulness or Meditation**  \n   Mindfulness exercises or meditation can help calm your mind and ease emotional pain. Focus on the present moment rather than dwelling on the past.\n\n8. **Limit Negative Influences**  \n   Avoid things that trigger sadness or anxiety, like social media or certain conversations. Surround yourself with positivity instead.\n\n9. **Consider Professional Help**  \n   If the pain feels overwhelming or persistent, a therapist or counselor can provide guidance and tools to help you heal.\n\n10. **Remember, Healing Takes Time**  \n   There\u2019s no quick fix for a broken heart. Be patient with yourself and trust that, with time, the pain will lessen.\n\nYou are stronger than you know, and brighter days are ahead. Sending you love and strength as you work through this. \u2764\ufe0f",
  "temperature": 1.0,
